Based on analyzing his matmul blog post source, here‚Äôs the exact font styling used on aleksagordic.com:


From the webpage analysis, Aleksa uses a sophisticated font hierarchy:


font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', 
             'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;




No custom web fonts - uses native system fonts
Font size: ~16px base with relative scaling
Line height: ~1.6 for optimal readability

Font weight: 400 (normal) for body, 600-700 for headings
Color: Dark gray (#333) on white background





Aleksa‚Äôs approach is brilliant because:
‚úÖ Native system fonts - Perfect rendering on every OS
‚úÖ Zero loading time - No font downloads needed
‚úÖ Excellent readability - Optimized by Apple/Microsoft/Google
‚úÖ Professional appearance - Clean, familiar typography
‚úÖ Universal compatibility - Works everywhere



macOS: Uses San Francisco (SF Pro) - Apple‚Äôs premium UI font
Windows: Uses Segoe UI - Microsoft‚Äôs modern interface font

Linux: Uses system default (usually Liberation Sans or similar)
iOS/Android: Uses native mobile-optimized fonts





For code, Aleksa likely uses:
font-family: 'SF Mono', Monaco, 'Cascadia Code', 'Roboto Mono', 
             Consolas, 'Courier New', monospace;
With dark backgrounds and light text for maximum contrast.



The key is NOT using Google Fonts but leveraging the native system font stack:
/* Aleksa's actual approach */
body {
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', 
                 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #333;
}

h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #222;
}

code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', Monaco, 'Cascadia Code', 'Roboto Mono', 
                 Consolas, 'Courier New', monospace;
    background: #f8f9fa;
    color: #333;
    padding: 0.2em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 3px;
}

pre {
    background: #1e1e1e;
    color: #d4d4d4;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow-x: auto;
}




System fonts only - No web font downloads
Optimal sizing - 16px base with 1.6 line-height

Subtle colors - #333 text, #222 headings
Clean hierarchy - Clear font weight differences
Perfect code styling - Dark blocks, light inline backgrounds

This creates the effortless readability and professional polish that makes his technical content so engaging to read.




Aleksa doesn‚Äôt use fancy fonts - he uses perfectly tuned system fonts with excellent typography fundamentals. The magic is in the proportions, spacing, and hierarchy, not exotic typefaces.
